@NoahStahl Dug into this a little bit more with help from @eerhardt.

It appears that the crux of the issue is related to the fact that when you use `CreateSlimBuilder`, we don't execute the code paths that register the [ManifestStaticWebAssetFileProvider](https://source.dot.net/Microsoft.AspNetCore.Hosting/R/c13feb527fc74de2.html) provider into the application. Ultimately, this is the `IFileProvider` implementation that handles resolving static assets using the manifest-based strategy vs. resolving them by searching directly on disk.

To resolve this issue, you'll want to wire up the correct file providers manually:

```csharp
var builder = WebApplication.CreateSlimBuilder(args);

builder.WebHost.UseStaticWebAssets();
```

This issue affects both the `MapStaticAssets` and `UseStaticFiles` strategies in .NET 9 so workarounds will be needed for both.

I'll put this in the backlog for now to evaluate urgency for a fix while the workaround is out.

