@javiercn Yeah correct, something is not working.

During development, sources in the web root are changed, while the application is already running and not restarted. Hence, files change while the application runs.

These files are used in the application and are served with hash values. These hash values obviously must match the files that are served.

To achieve this, we use something like the following:

```csharp
string GetHash(IWebHostEnvironment env, IMemoryCache cache, string path)
{
    if (cache.TryGetValue(path, out var hash))
    {
        var fileProvider = env.WebRootFileProvider;

        var cacheEntryOptions = new MemoryCacheEntryOptions();

        // this is apparently not working, since the cache entry never expires
        cacheEntryOptions.AddExpirationToken(fileProvider.Watch(path));

        hash = ...

        cache.Set(path, hash, cacheEntryOptions);
    }
    return hash;
}
```

Sadly, that is not working, since the cache entry never expires.

